{{Quote|They're bugs, sir. Several centimeters long. Travel in swarms of up to twenty or more. ''Challat'' is the Xexto's word for flesh. They're predators, sir!|[[Jace Dallin]]|<ref name="Star Wars (1998) 38">[[Star Wars (1998) 38|''Star Wars'' (1998) 38]]</ref>}}
'''Challat eaters''' were vicious, swarming predators found on [[Troiken/Legends|Troiken]]. They preyed upon the native [[Xexto/Legends|Xexto]] population; they were carnivorous and devoured the flesh of anything they came into contact with. Challat eaters were small in size and glowed bright blue.

[[File:Challat_eater_swarm.jpg|thumb|left|235px|A swarm of challat eaters attack [[Stark Commercial Combine]] forces trapped within [[Troiken]]'s [[Mount Avos]] caves at the end of the [[Stark Hyperspace War/Legends|Stark Hyperspace War]] of [[44 BBY/Legends|44 BBY]].]]

They provided some trouble for the [[Outland Regions Security Force/Legends|Republic force]] trapped in [[Mount Avos]] during the [[Stark Hyperspace War/Legends|Stark Hyperspace War]], and after [[Ranulph Tarkin/Legends|Ranulph Tarkin]] destroyed the barrier erected by the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] to keep them out, they consumed the [[Stark Commercial Combine|Stark Collective]] force that the Jedi trapped within the mountain stronghold after they were forced to seal it off.

[[Tsian]] used [[Challat eater droid|droids modeled after the insects]] in her assassinations.

"Challat" meant flesh in [[Xextese]].

[[File:Challat_eaters_confront_Kenobi_Vos.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Jedi Padawans [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Quinlan Vos/Legends|Quinlan Vos]] encounter challat eaters in the Mount Avos caves during the Stark Hyperspace conflict.]]

